    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Whose Free Speech?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>John A Friede letter, commenting on April 16 article, says McCain-Feingold campaign finance bill is greatest threat to freedom of expression since McCarthy era</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I have no objection to the loosening of ownership limits on media companies, but your April 16 front-page article referring to ''the free-speech rights of corporations'' stopped me short. With your enthusiastic support, the greatest threat to freedom of expression since the McCarthy era is being foisted on the American people in the form of the McCain-Feingold campaign finance bill.</p>
        <p>JOHN A. FRIEDE  Rye, N.Y., April 16, 2001</p>
      </block>
